<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 1094
                    The Representative on the Allied Commission on
                        Reparations (
                        Pauley
                    ) to the Acting Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv02</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1094</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1094</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-07-17T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-07-17T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1094" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1094">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Potsdam/7–1745: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1094<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative on the Allied Commission on
                        Reparations</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PEW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pauley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-17">July 17,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Victory1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi>
                    </gloss>–51. To <persName corresp="#p_KMCP1">Kindleberger</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_WJR1">Wolf</persName>, White House, Washington for
                    [Acting] Secretary of State from <persName corresp="#p_PEW1">Pauley</persName>.</p>
                <p>Understand that <persName corresp="#p_RJJ1">Reinstein</persName> has been
                    preparing materials on possible Italian reparations and restitutions. Urgently
                    require outstanding features of this report. Cable summary to me at Tripartite
                    Conference Headquarters <gloss target="#t_Masterwork1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Masterwork</hi>
                    </gloss> Berlin with particular emphasis upon what might be available for
                    reparations and possible value of same. Send also estimates made by State and
                        <gloss target="#t_FEA1">FEA</gloss> as to value of imports required by Italy
                    in order to maintain her economy over the coming year. (Repeat message for
                        <persName corresp="#p_SRG1">Sproul</persName>, c/o American Delegation,
                    Allied Commission on Reparations, American Embassy, Moscow, for his information
                    numbering the repeat message as follows <gloss target="#t_Confrep1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Confrep</hi>
                    </gloss> 3.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
